HEADWORD: Deiform
<hw>De"i*form</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>deus</ets>
a god + <ets>-form</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Godlike, or of a
godlike form.</def> <rj><au>Dr. H. More.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Conformable to the will of God.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Burnet.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deiformity</ent>⟦br⟧
